Let f : [$$-$$3, 1] $$ \to $$ R be given as <br><br>$$f(x) = \left\{ \matrix{
  \min \,\{ (x + 6),{x^2}\}, - 3 \le x \le 0 \hfill \cr 
  \max \,\{ \sqrt x ,{x^2}\} ,\,0 \le x \le 1. \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br><br>If the area bounded by y = f(x) and x-axis is A, then the value of 6A is equal to ___________.
